class Solution {
    public int minOperations(int n) {
        int count = 0;
        while (n > 0) {
            if ((n & (n - 1)) == 0) {
                break;
            }
            n &= (n - 1);
            count++;
        }
        return count + 1;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution uses bitwise operations to find the minimum number of operations to make n equal to 0. It works by continuously clearing the least significant bit of n until n becomes a power of 2, then one more operation is needed to make n equal to 0.

